  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Photographic negative</ab>
      <ab type="lido:event" subtype="creation">
        <date>1934-11-30</date>
      <persName role="Press Photographer"><forename>Namık</forename><surname>Görgüç</surname><ref type="context" target="info:fedora/context:siba.pn.7d5d8ec5">Görgüç, Namık</ref></persName><persName role="Press Photographer"><forename>Selahattin </forename><surname>Giz</surname><ref type="context" target="info:fedora/context:siba.pn.dce0efc3">Giz, Selahattin </ref></persName></ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Spectators are lined up along a playing field. Close up, a man with a moustache and flat cap turns his head to the photographer. Further off, a young man in a student cap is chewing on something. The background consists of a stand full of spectators standing against the wall of an old building displaying a large billboard.</ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet" subtype="comment">The photograph was taken in the context of a sports article in Cumhuriyet. The specators are watching the Galatasaray vs. Fenerbahçe football game in <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=T3">Taksim stadı</ref> on 30 November 1930. The article gives an attendance figure of close to five thousand. The game ended in a 0-0 draw.</ab>
